10/10/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- The police announced on Friday (October 8th) that 177 people are facing charges as part of an investigation aimed to bust child pornography over the internet. 
They are accused of possessing or distributing child pornography via the web. 
Eighteen people have been arrested in the probe. 
Sixteen of them are Greek, and the remaining two are foreigners. 
The four-month investigation, code-named Operation Sledgehammer, was carried out in co-operation with foreign police. 
Civil servants, businessmen, a schoolteacher and a sketch artist are among the suspects. 
(AP, DPA, ANA-MPA - 08/10/10)
